# Getting Started
To start using DecimalSystem, head over to [Installation](/docs/install) to install it, then take a look at [Num](/docs/num) to learn how to use it. You can also view the below examples:

##### 

## Examples
### Convert a number to base 16
```javascript
runkitconst {Num} = require("decimalsystem");

new Num(123).toBase(16).toString();
```
#### 
### Convert a base 16 number to base 10
```javascript
runkitconst {Num} = require("decimalsystem");

new Num({num: "7b", base: 16}).toBase(10).toString();
```

##### 

### Convert a number to base 2.5
```javascript
runkitconst {Num} = require("decimalsystem");

new Num(17).toBase(2.5).toString();
```
#### 
### Convert a base 2.5 number to base 10
```javascript
runkitconst {Num} = require("decimalsystem");

new Num({num: "1001.0202002", base: 2.5}).toBase(10).toString();
```
##### 

### Convert a number to base PI
```javascript
runkitconst {Num} = require("decimalsystem");

new Num(54).toBase(Math.PI).toString();
```
#### 
### Convert a base PI number to base 10
```javascript
runkitconst {Num} = require("decimalsystem");

new Num({num: "1210.01010102", base: Math.PI}).toBase(10).toString();
```
